<% cache(:faq) do %>
<div class="hero-unit faq">
    <div class="ac">
      <h1>FAQ</h1><br />
      <p>Answers to frequently asked questions.</p>
      <input type="text" value="" placeholder="Search ..." />
      <a type="" class="search_button btn btn-success"><i class="icon-search icon-white"></i></a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <ul>
      <li>
        <h3>How do You keep my personal information safe?</h3>
        <p>All information is transmitted over encrypted connection with the browser.  Your information is stored in our database which is secured with encryption as well.  We will never give out your medication information except to you and your assigned clinic.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>How do I change my password?</h3>
        <p>Click the sign in button in the upper right and then click the 'Forgot your password?' link below the sign in form.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>How do I cancel my account?</h3>
        <p>Just send an email to admin@medpasses.com from the email address you used to sign up and we will delete your information.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>How do I invite friends?</h3>
        <p>Send them a link to <a href="https://www.medpasses.com/users/sign_up">our sign up page</a>.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>What does https:// mean?</h3>
        <p>It means there is a secure connection between your browser and our server.  We ensure this for every connection to prevent accidental leakage of your information.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>How do I upgrade my plan?</h3>
        <p>Lobby your clinic to sign up for the program and you will automatically be included.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>How do I set up notifications?</h3>
        <p>When viewing your medication list just click on the 'Add to Passbook' button beside the medication you want to add and then accept the pass.  The pass will automatically receive notifications via a secure, encrypted connection.  Push notifications are sent for the pass from Apple's servers.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Why do I get 404 error?</h3>
        <p>You tried to access a page that doesn't exist.  Keep trying!  You're sure to get it eventually, or use the links above.</p>
      </li>

    </ul>

    <h3 class="no-results hidden well">No results matching your search.</h3>
    <br /><br /><br />

  </div>


  </div>
  <% end %>